Czarnówka  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Wydminy, within Giżycko County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It lies approximately  east of Wydminy,  east of Giżycko, and  east of the regional capital Olsztyn. As of the 2021 census, Czarnówka had a population of 87 residents. The village covers an area of 8.44 square kilometers.
